race.comment: DIAMOND EPIC (7) was in great form before a one paced effort latest at Doomben when sat close and was outdashed. Suspect will be ridden colder here and with the low draw and claim should be winding up strongly. GORBACHEV (4) was a close-up third here fresh then a narrow winner at Doomben last time. Speedy galloper who will take catching despite the wide gate. ROSE OF SHIRAZ (8) was a Class 3 winner here two back then raced on speed and fought on well to just miss last time out. Looks well placed with the claim and expected to feature again. FARWEST (5) has good form over the longer trip but is fitter for a trial and does have good fresh form. With plenty of pace on up front expected to be winding up late.
